                  </hi>. I live at Road-green, near Royston, in Hertfordshire. On 20th June, about 11 o'clock, I was in Fenchurch-street, and felt something behind me—I turned round, and saw the prisoner doubling my handkerchief up in his hand—I collared him, took it from him, and took him to the station.</p>
